# Implementation Plan — Loose/Bulk Items & Special Discounts

This plan details the full implementation of the two features described in the [feature_suggestions.md](file:///C:/Users/ABCD/.gemini/antigravity-ide/brain/5b9bf0f4-ef62-4002-a8e9-6630eb5ce025/feature_suggestions.md) document:
1. **Per-Item Special Discounts** (including staff caps)
2. **Bulk/Loose Items** (decimal quantities, custom weights, grams input, kg internal tracking)

To ensure consistency and safety, we will structure this in two logical phases:
- **Phase 1: Special Discounts** (Backend models, routes, billing validations, UI inputs, receipt additions, and analytics prep)
- **Phase 2: Loose/Bulk Items** (Migration of quantities to numeric types, PG stored function updates, product type additions, weight entry interface, and decimal stock log changes)

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Schema Changes (Decimals)**: To support loose items like Almonds/Cashews sold by weight (e.g., 250g = 0.250 kg), we are modifying the data types of quantity columns (`qty`, `stock_qty`, etc.) from `INTEGER` to `NUMERIC(10,3)`. This is a database-wide change that affects products, inventory adjustments, purchase order items, billing, and EOD entries.
>
> **Staff Discount Cap**: By default, we will introduce a configurable staff discount cap key in `store_settings` named `staff_max_discount_cap` (defaults to ₹50 per item). If a user with role `staff` attempts to apply a discount greater than this cap on any single unit, the checkout request will be rejected. The store owner (`owner` role) has unlimited discount privileges.

